<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-08-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-08-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="463" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d463">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 800.51/10</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Acting Secretary of the Treasury</hi>
                                    (<persName corresp="#p_COT1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Crosby</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-08-06">
                                        <hi rend="italic">August 6, 1917</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I beg to advise you that a credit of
                                $160,000,000 was a few days ago established in favor of the French
                                Government for the month of August, under which advances of
                                $8,000,000 and $32,000,000 were made on August 3 and August 6, 1917,
                                respectively.</p>
                            <pb facs="0635" n="561" xml:id="pg_561"/>
                            <p>I also beg to advise you that an additional loan of $10,000,000 was
                                to-day made to the Italian Government under the credit of
                                $60,000,000 established in its favor on July 5, of which you have
                                already been notified.</p>
                            <p>For your convenience, I am inserting the following tabulation of
                                credits and loans to date to foreign Governments under the act of
                                April 24,1917: <table cols="4" rend="bordered" rows="10">
                                    <row>
                                        <cell>Country</cell>
                                        <cell>Loans and credits agreed upon</cell>
                                        <cell>Loans made</cell>
                                        <cell>Balance under established credits</cell>
                                    </row>
                                    <row>
                                        <cell>Great Britain</cell>
                                        <cell role="num">$955,000,000</cell>
                                        <cell role="num">$820,000,000</cell>
                                        <cell role="num">$135,000,000</cell>
                                    </row>
                                    <row>
                                        <cell>France</cell>
                                        <cell role="num">530,000,000</cell>
                                        <cell role="num">410,000,000</cell>
                                        <cell role="num">120,000,000</cell>
                                    </row>
                                    <row>
                                        <cell>Italy</cell>
                                        <cell role="num">160,000,000</cell>
                                        <cell role="num">140,000,000</cell>
                                        <cell role="num">20,000,000</cell>
                                    </row>
                                    <row>
                                        <cell>Russia</cell>
                                        <cell role="num">100,000,000</cell>
                                        <cell role="num">37,500,000</cell>
                                        <cell role="num">62,500,000</cell>
                                    </row>
                                    <row>
                                        <cell>Russia</cell>
                                        <cell role="num">75,000,000</cell>
                                        <cell role="num">10,000,000</cell>
                                        <cell role="num">65,000,000</cell>
                                    </row>
                                    <row>
                                        <cell>Belgium</cell>
                                        <cell role="num">45,000,000</cell>
                                        <cell role="num">22,500,000</cell>
                                        <cell role="num">22,500,000</cell>
                                    </row>
                                    <row>
                                        <cell>Belgium</cell>
                                        <cell role="num">2,500,000</cell>
                                        <cell role="num">1,000,000</cell>
                                        <cell role="num">1,500,000</cell>
                                    </row>
                                    <row>
                                        <cell>Serbia</cell>
                                        <cell role="num">3,000,000</cell>
                                        <cell role="num">1,000,000</cell>
                                        <cell role="num">2,000,000</cell>
                                    </row>
                                    <row>
                                        <cell>Totals</cell>
                                        <cell role="num">1,870,500,000</cell>
                                        <cell role="num">1,442,000,000</cell>
                                        <cell role="num">428,500,000</cell>
                                    </row>
                                </table>
                            </p>
                            <p>Respectfully,</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_COT1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Oscar T. Crosby</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>